{
  "analysis": "The diagnostics show `BH` is installed in `/usr/lib/R/site-library`, while `rstan` and `StanHeaders` are in `/usr/local/lib/R/site-library`. `.libPaths()` includes both, so `BH` is visible. The error string “Boost not found” was not found in the installed rstan package by grep, which suggests it may come from `pkgbuild`/compilation configuration or a different helper. I need inspect how `stan_model` builds include flags and where the error originates.",
  "plan": "I will search the installed rstan and pkgbuild R source files for Boost/BoostDir logic and the exact error message. I will also run a minimal `stan_model` call with `verbose=TRUE` and inspect `system.file` include paths to see what include flags are generated. This should reveal whether the issue is a missing `BH` system file path or a linker/include detection bug.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -R \"Boost\" /usr/local/lib/R/site-library/rstan/R /usr/local/lib/R/site-library/rstan/include 2>/dev/null | head -80\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -R \"Boost not found\\|BoostDir\\|boost_not_in_BH\\|BH\" /usr/local/lib/R/site-library/rstan/R /usr/local/lib/R/site-library/rstan/inst 2>/dev/null | head -120\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -R \"Boost not found\\|BoostDir\\|boost_not_in_BH\\|system.file.*BH\\|package.*BH\" /usr/lib/R/site-library/pkgbuild /usr/local/lib/R/site-library/pkgbuild 2>/dev/null | head -120\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "Rscript -e 'library(rstan); cat(\"BH system include:\", system.file(\"include\", package=\"BH\"), \"\\n\"); cat(\"StanHeaders src:\", system.file(\"include\", \"src\", package=\"StanHeaders\"), \"\\n\"); tryCatch(stan_model(file=\"/app/hierarchical_model.stan\", verbose=TRUE), error=function(e) print(e))' 2>&1 | tail -120\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    }
  ]
}
